            <thetext>As of now, many of the framework config.json and Manifest.json files contain javascript-style comments. These are illegal according to the json specification (will supply citation if needed). Thus, trying to parse these json files with external tools results in errors.

I would suggest that these comments should be deprecated and automatically removed during the migration to a next major version. A spec-compliant alternative could be to introduce a &quot;comment&quot; key that is ignored during the parsing of the file.</thetext>
